                <p>This is usually caused by a faulty control board or sensor not detecting the cycle's end. A quick diagnostic can pinpoint the issue.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="My Samsung washer is shaking excessively—what's wrong?">
                <p>This can result from unbalanced loads, worn suspension rods, or damaged shock absorbers. We'll inspect the drum and leveling system.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="What do Samsung washer error codes mean?">
                <p>Codes like 4E (water supply issue), 5E (drain error), or UE (unbalanced load) indicate specific component malfunctions.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
